{{Blurimage|align=right|file=Empty-parking-lot-with-street-lights-at-night-.jpg|caption=The first image of Level 136.}} 
==Description==
'''Level 136''' manifests as a vast, outdoor parking lot kept in a state of perpetual starless night. The pavement is often wet, as if it had just rained, with scattered puddles on the ground. Water drops from light poles and canopies, but no rainfall occurs. The level is barren, and no vehicles are ever present. The only features are scattered streetlights, canopies, curbs, and dividers with sparse greenery. Scattered objects have been found in the level without any clear purpose.<ref>These objects include paint buckets, umbrellas and various litter.</ref> A light fog frequently obscures the level, muting visibility.

Most of '''Level 136''' is visually identical, contributing to a repetitive and unvarying environment. Even natural features such as trees appear nearly identical. Variations that do exist are usually minor. The level has no clouds or stars and has been described both with and without a moon.<ref>Why the moon is not always present is unclear.</ref> Periodically a dark forest can be seen in the distance. It is impossible to reach this forest, and it will always remain in the distance. On occasion the streetlights will have abnormal color shades, such as deep red or green. No meaning to most of these colors has been determined, but touching a lone blue light exits the level. Other strange anomalies have been found in the level, such as floating objects and street signs with warnings depicting entities in the Backrooms. None of these entities have been observed in '''Level 136'''. 

The temperature of  '''Level 136''' sits around 10°C, made cooler by a light breeze that permeates the level. Sounds behave unnaturally in the level, echoing in ways that don’t fit the environment or direction the sound came from. '''Level 136''' is affected by [[Phenomenon 15]], preventing wanderers from encountering one another. The level can induce mild mental effects on its inhabitants; commonly reported feelings include loneliness, emptiness, and disconnection. Several wanderers have described a loss of purpose when present in this level.

'''Level 136''' has minimal dangers present and is safe for a short-term stay; however, while water can be found as puddles, there is no food or almond water, making a prolonged stay unviable. Additionally, there is The Frozen Lots and an event called The Collapse; both can be dangerous if a wanderer is caught unprepared.
===Areas===
{{Blurimage|caption=An image of The Frozen Lots|file=Snowy lot.png|align=right}}
<div style="color:#57daff;">'''The Frozen Lots'''</div>
By traveling against '''Level 136's''' breeze, it is possible to reach a snow-covered area within the level. The foliage is dormant or evergreen, and the streetlights are often faulty, resulting in dim sections. Snow mounds are scattered throughout, and icicles hang from the canopies. Frozen puddles cover portions of the ground, creating a slipping hazard. Snowmen have been encountered in the Frozen Lots; while they appear as ordinary snowmen, they anomalously move when unobserved. The snowmen have never been seen acting aggressive or following a wanderer, instead moving in random patterns. A small portion of the snowmen have an atypical appearance, being snow replicas of entities, unidentifiable masses, and some being made of solid ice rather than snow. The temperature in this area drops to -5°C, and the breeze grows slightly stronger. Compared to the rest of the level, this area is significantly more dangerous due to the frigid temperatures and slippery ground.
<div style="color:#87837b;">'''The Overcast Lots'''</div>
The Overcast Lots are small areas found periodically throughout '''Level 136'''. Although it is daytime, a thick layer of clouds blocks out both the sky and sun, creating a gray and low-saturation environment.<ref> One wanderer stated that they experienced the sun breaking through the clouds. This experience caused the wanderer to feel immense terror and dread, as if this event wasn't supposed to happen. The phenomenon lasted a few moments before the sun was blocked by clouds again.</ref>The winds are stronger in the Overcast Lots than other areas, capable of sweeping loose items across the ground. The pavement in the area is dry with moderate cracking, and the parking spaces are faded. The ground is cluttered with debris such as sticks, leaves, and litter. Distant thunder has been heard; despite this, no lightning has been observed. Other anomalies unique to this area include faint wind chimes, echoing tornado sirens, and items blowing against the wind. The strangest anomaly found is towers of clouds that extend to the ground. These clouds are not tornadic and merely obscure sight and impede movement. While an individual is inside one of the clouds, sound entirely cuts out. Not even one's own breathing can be heard.

===The Collapse===
Rarely, the level contracts dramatically, as darkness closes around the wanderer, obscuring the level and leaving a small, confined space of varying size. At its edges lies a drop into a black void. Falling results in permanent disappearance. Where the drop leads is unknown, but many believe that it is [[The Void]]. This state may last anywhere from a few minutes to several hours before the level expands back to its original sprawl. During The Collapse, various anomalies may occur, ranging from physical distortions to hallucinations. Common experiences include flickering lights, melting surroundings, color desaturation, and unintelligible voices. Some wanderers have reported seeing other levels in the distance during The Collapse. The validity of these claims is disputed, and they may just be hallucinations.
==Addendum==
This is a section of a journal entry retrieved in [[Level 450]] that first described '''Level 136'''. Wanderer’s fate unknown.
<div style="background-color:#F5D9A7; color: black; margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:2px solid #000000; border-radius: 3px"> 

<div style="font-family:Caveat">
…I dashed through the doorway and entered a tight corridor, [[Entity 3|the creature’s]] laughter mocking me. Then I saw it: an elevator at the end of the hall.

I rushed into the elevator and closed the doors just in time. I could hear the creature’s cackles echoing through the door. As the elevator headed upwards, I tried to gather my thoughts and make a plan, but I only had respite for a couple minutes. The elevator interrupted my thoughts as it opened its doors, bringing me to a new location. Like [[Level 1|the place]] I’d just escaped, it was a large parking lot, but this one was outdoors, like those outside big-box stores. The atmosphere was dark and gloomy, and puddles covered the ground as if it had just rained, reflecting the harsh glow from streetlights. The humid air was in stark contrast to the stagnant atmosphere of the last place. As I stepped out of the elevator, it disappeared behind me, leaving me alone in an empty landscape with no clear path ahead.

Without any other options, I chose a direction and walked. I must’ve walked for hours wandering this place. The moment I fell into this nightmare replayed continuously in my head. One second I was opening my front door, and the next I was someplace else. The walls were old and yellow, and an obnoxious buzzing flooded my ears. With every step I took, the more homesick I grew. I couldn’t stop seeing the faces of my wife and kids, which made me long more than ever to make it home.

Suddenly the lampposts began to flicker, and a complete darkness enveloped my surroundings. I walked towards the wall of darkness until I reached the edge of the visible environment. There I found a deep chasm, which dropped into a black void. I tried to go a different way, but the darkness had engulfed every direction. Then unintelligible voices began to whisper in my head. They felt like intrusive thoughts that wouldn’t go away. A small part of me wondered if I should just jump; if this was a dream, maybe I would wake up.

After what felt like an eternity, the darkness receded. In the distance a lamppost with a calming blue light called to me. Almost in a trance, I reached out and touched it. At that moment, I was transported, left standing in an empty traffic circle, with highways surrounding me stretching endlessly into a misty fog. Whatever this place might be, there has to be a way out…
</div>
</div>

==Entrances and Exits==
{{Blurimage|file=Foggy parking lot.webp|caption=An image of the level with fog.|align=right}}
===Entrances===
* Finding automatic door in [[Level 499]] leads to this level.
* Using an elevator in [[Level 1]] may transport one to this level.
* Encountering an out of place streetlight in [[Level 135]] can signal a transition to this level.
* Walking on a pavement path in [[Level 135.1]] leads here.

===Exits===
* The most consistent exit manifests as a dimly lit storefront. Entering it leads to [[Level 197]].
* No-clipping out of this level results in transportation to any of [[Special:RandomInCategory/The_Main_Nine|The Main Nine]]. The best locations to no-clip are strange anomalies such as tilted poles in the ground.
* Touching a lone streetlight emitting blue light results in entering [[Level 690]].
* After walking long enough, it is possible to reach a wall of rain. Continuing through it leads to [[Level 124]].
* Rarely, after the collapse, a library can come into view. Entering leads to [[The End]].
*
* Other less common exits may exist but are unconfirmed.











