{{DatabaseLoginForm|'''The following file was received by Team D-1 by an anonymous wanderer on 5/09/20XX.'''

Greetings, Major Warren.

This message is to inform you of a dangerous anomaly I've encountered within Level 136. As you know, the level is affected by Phenomenon 15, and as such, no entities have been documented. However, this has changed, as I've just had an encounter with a Duller while venturing in Level 136. I don't know how it got there, but more entities could begin entering. 

I've been attacked by Dullers before, but this one was different. It was stronger, seemed smarter, and could even speak. The hallucinations it produced were more vivid and realistic compared to other Dullers. Despite having trained myself to resist Duller illusions, I failed to do so with this one. With other Dullers, you can find cracks in their illusions and break free with a strong mental fortitude, but this one was too powerful. 

The Duller spoke to me inside my head, like an intrusive thought, with a gruff, resentful-sounding voice; it sounded angered, but at what I'm not sure. At times its anger was entirely directed at me, but other times it seemed furious at something else. The only reason I survived is because I was fortunate enough to accidentally no-clip out of Level 136 into Level 0.

After giving it some thought, I believe that this Duller may be a figure known as 'The King.' I have talked to others who brought to my attention the "Kingsmeal" theory, which I now wholeheartedly believe. The theory suggests that Dullers are a hivemind controlled by a leader called 'The King,' an individual that I think may be the Duller I was attacked by. 

I request that you have your team investigate Level 136 and the Duller. While Level 136 may not be an important level, other safe levels in The Backrooms have fallen in the past, and this could be the start of another collapse of safe havens.

— anonymous}}

